    "body": "Attaching back to the parent’s console handle can also make the console fail to exit because a Windows subsystem application is still attached to it. This happens when you run `code` from `cmd` and then type in `exit`. CMD exits and the window remains because VSCode reattaches to its parent’s console handle. ",
